<subSubSection id="C325650CBD32FFD993D7953EFCDCFA23" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B803687BD32FFD993D7953EFE93FABD" blockId="40.[189,324,1319,1345]" box="[189,324,1319,1345]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<heading id="D0C881EBBD32FFD993D7953EFE93FABD" bold="true" box="[189,324,1319,1345]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD993D7953EFE93FABD" bold="true" box="[189,324,1319,1345]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B803687BD32FFD993D7954EFCDCFA23" blockId="40.[189,1398,1367,1504]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
This genus is dedicated to Chung Cheng Lu (Museum of 
<collectingRegion id="49FBF865BD32FFD99006954EFC19FA8D" box="[876,974,1367,1393]" country="Australia" name="Victoria" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Victoria</collectingRegion>
, Melbourne, 
<collectingCountry id="F3287617BD32FFD99700954EFB01FA8D" box="[1130,1238,1367,1393]" name="Australia" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Australia</collectingCountry>
and National Chung Hsing University, Taichung, Taiwan), in recognition of his enormous contribution to teuthology, including 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD9925D95B9FE64FA46" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[311,435,1440,1466]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sepiolinae">Sepiolinae</taxonomicName>
systematics; its name derives from the combination of Lu’s family name with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD993D795DCFEC2FA23" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[189,277,1477,1503]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Sepiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD993D795DCFEC2FA23" box="[189,277,1477,1503]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Sepiola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a closely related genus. Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C325650CBD32FFD993D79611FEDEF817" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B803687BD32FFD993D79611FE03F9DE" blockId="40.[189,468,1544,1570]" box="[189,468,1544,1570]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
