<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD993D79611FE03F9DE" bold="true" box="[189,468,1544,1570]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Discussion of affinities</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B803687BD32FFD993D79621FAEFF8D3" blockId="40.[189,1399,1592,1839]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD993D79621FEE6F9AE" authority="Bello, 2020" authorityName="Bello" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,305,1592,1618]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Lusepiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD993D79621FEE6F9AE" box="[189,305,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Lusepiola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27857EEBD32FFD992519620FE7BF9AF" box="[315,428,1593,1619]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD992D19620FDE2F9AE" authorityName="Steenstrup" authorityYear="1887" box="[443,565,1593,1618]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Euprymna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD992D19620FDE2F9AE" box="[443,565,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Euprymna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD9912D9621FD13F9AE" authority="Bello, 2020" authorityName="Bello" authorityYear="2020" box="[583,708,1592,1618]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Eumandya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD9912D9621FD13F9AE" box="[583,708,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Eumandya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27857EEBD32FFD991BA9620FCE9F9AF" box="[720,830,1593,1619]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD990179621FBD1F9AE" authority="Bello, 2020" authorityName="Bello" authorityYear="2020" box="[893,1030,1592,1618]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Boletzkyola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD990179621FBD1F9AE" box="[893,1030,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Boletzkyola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27857EEBD32FFD9977B9620FBA8F9AF" box="[1041,1151,1593,1619]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
all possess a closed bursa copularix, a clear indication of their affinity. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD990E79644FBD6F98B" authority="Bello, 2020" authorityName="Bello" authorityYear="2020" box="[909,1025,1629,1655]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Lusepiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD990E79644FBD6F98B" box="[909,1025,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Lusepiola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27857EEBD32FFD997629644FBA4F98B" box="[1032,1139,1629,1655]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the other three genera because the formation of its hectocotylus copulatory apparatus involves modified sucker pedicels from both the ventral and dorsal rows. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD990F196BFFC24F93C" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[923,1011,1702,1728]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Sepiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD990F196BFFC24F93C" box="[923,1011,1702,1728]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Sepiola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27857EEBD32FFD9909096BEFBF7F93D" box="[1018,1056,1703,1729]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from which its species were removed, primarily because of the different 
<typeStatus id="54848825BD32FFD991BF96D2FCDFF919" box="[725,776,1739,1765]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">type</typeStatus>
of bursa copulatrix; moreover, the basal part of its hectocotylus bears four suckers (two complete rows) instead of three. The peculiarly modified pedicels in the distal part of the hectocotylus separates 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD991B1970DFC98F8D2" authority="Bello, 2020" authorityName="Bello" authorityYear="2020" box="[731,847,1812,1838]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Lusepiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD991B1970DFC98F8D2" box="[731,847,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Lusepiola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27857EEBD32FFD9903D970CFC16F8D3" box="[855,961,1813,1839]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from all other sepioline genera.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B803687BD32FFD993D7974EFEF8F88D" blockId="40.[189,303,1879,1905]" box="[189,303,1879,1905]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<heading id="D0C881EBBD32FFD993D7974EFEF8F88D" bold="true" box="[189,303,1879,1905]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD993D7974EFEF8F88D" bold="true" box="[189,303,1879,1905]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B803687BD32FFD993D7979EFEDEF817" blockId="40.[189,1399,1927,2027]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
The species in this genus, namely 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD991259791FD35F85D" authorityName="Bello" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Sasaki" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[591,738,1927,1953]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Lusepiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="birostrata" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD991259791FD35F85D" box="[591,738,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">L. birostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27857EEBD32FFD991839791FC17F85E" box="[745,960,1927,1954]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D04BD32FFD990939791FB46F85D" authorityName="Bello" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Voss" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1017,1169,1928,1953]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Sepiolidae" genus="Sepiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sepiolida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="trirostrata" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94BEA95BD32FFD990939791FB46F85D" box="[1017,1169,1928,1953]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">L. trirostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27857EEBD32FFD997F29791FAA5F85E" box="[1176,1394,1927,1954]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, are distributed in the western Pacific from the Okhotsk Sea to 
<collectingCountry id="F3287617BD32FFD990F597B5FBC1F83A" box="[927,1046,1964,1990]" name="Singapore" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Singapore</collectingCountry>
(Reid &amp; Jereb 2005; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B76BD32FFD9967297B5FF2FF817" author="Okutani T." pageId="40" pageNumber="41" refId="ref28381" refString="Okutani T. 2015. Cuttlefishes and Squids of the World (New Edition). Tokai University Press, Tokay." type="book" year="2015">Okutani 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
